cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with the implementation of an acoustic room simulator. It could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it discusses the use of deep neural networks for speech recognition. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves optimizing the performance of a system. It may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the training of deep neural networks. Finally, it could be classified under cs.SI (Signal Processing) as it involves processing audio signals.
